The Abuja Enterprise Agency (AEA) is set to hold the Mask-Up Abuja Challenge to foster innovation and growth in the FCT. The Mask-Up Abuja Challenge is largely a virtual competition initiated by the Abuja Enterprise Agency to support MSMEs in taking up leading roles in the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic. A statement by the Public Relations Officer of the agency, Ifeyinwa Amulu, said the challenge is conceived as a platform to revive economic activities in the creative industry specifically the fashion sector to bring about innovative designs of face masks, which is a key component of the government social distancing guidelines. “Thus, the Mask-Up Abuja Challenge is the agency’s contribution towards bolstering the FCT Administration’s strategy in fighting the COVID-19 pandemic by boosting the production of face mask, creating awareness for the use of face mask and increasing the supply of face mask in the FCT, “she said. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here It is open to fashion designers residing in the FCT between the ages of 18 – 45; submission of entries started 7th May and will close on 15th May 2020. The Grand finale will hold on 18th of May 2020 in Abuja, where shortlisted competitors will pitch their ideas to a panel of judges. The winners of the competition will be provided with cash prizes worth N1 million, 1 month free kiosk stand at choice location, free capacity building and mentorship programme with Vodi Fashion House. The virtual challenge is expected to create various opportunities for participants such as market linkage, access to grant, workspace, capacity building, credit facility, which will in turn facilitate business and boost employment.  COVID-19: FG decries flouting protective measures COVID-19: ‘FG closely monitoring Kano, Osun, Oyo, Edo’ Entrepreneurs urged to brace up for challenges